VD. Srinivas a highly talented veena artiste from Hyderabad presented a melodious  ensemble, at the International Environmentalists conference organised by the Department of Tourism,  at Chowmahalla palace. Srinivas who is a part of All India Radio, Hyderabad can easily blend classical ragas with western music without changing the mood of the raga. displayed a soothing ensemble in the company of Guru Prasad on the keyboard, Raju on the flute, Ramana Murthy on the mridangam and Premender on the tabla.The evening began with the raga Keeravani and it was then improvised on the Carnatic, Hindustani and Western styles by the artistes.They brought out all the different combinations ofswarapattern in Keeravani maintaining a fast runningchatrasra nadiby the percussion.Srinivas took Sindubhairavi in detail with goodragabhavamfollowed with a controlled and high speedtanam. Again the co- artistes joined the party by sharing theswaramin several permutations and combinations.  The concluding part of the ensemble includedThandanaa famous number of Annamacharya, followed byAdivo Alladivoand a Western composition by Maduramani Iyer.
